### Admin Hotel API Test Requests
### RESTful API endpoints for admin hotel management
### 
### Prerequisites:
### 1. Make sure the server is running (default: http://localhost:3000)
### 2. You need to be authenticated as admin/partner (session cookie required)
### 3. For authentication, login via /api/auth endpoints with partner role

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json

### Variables (update these with your actual values)
@hotelId = 1
@sessionCookie = your-session-cookie-here

###############################################
### HOTELS RESOURCE
###############################################

### GET /api/admin/hotels
### Get all hotels owned by the authenticated admin
### Query params: page (default: 1), limit (default: 20, max: 100)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/hotels?page=1&limit=20
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Cookie: connect.sid={{sessionCookie}}

###

### GET /api/admin/hotels (With pagination)
### Get hotels with custom pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/hotels?page=2&limit=10
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Cookie: connect.sid={{sessionCookie}}

###

### GET /api/admin/hotels/:hotelId
### Get a specific hotel by ID with rooms and statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/hotels/{{hotelId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Cookie: connect.sid={{sessionCookie}}

###

### GET /api/admin/hotels/:hotelId (Invalid - hotel not found)
### Should return 404 Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/hotels/99999
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Cookie: connect.sid={{sessionCookie}}

###

### PATCH /api/admin/hotels/:hotelId
### Update hotel information
### You can update any combination of fields
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/hotels/{{hotelId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Cookie: connect.sid={{sessionCookie}}

{
  "name": "Updated Hotel Name",
  "description": "Updated hotel description",
  "address": "123 Updated Street",
  "city": "Updated City",
  "country": "Updated Country",
  "phone_number": "+1234567890",
  "email": "updated@hotel.com",
  "star_rating": 4,
  "hotel_amenities": "WiFi, Pool, Gym, Spa"
}

